DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

do {
   $ans = random(2, 5, 1);
   $c1 = random(2, 5, 1);
   $c2 = random(2, 6, 1);
   $c3 = $ans * ($c1 + $c2);
} until $c3 <= 40;

do {
   $a = random(1, 9, 1);
} until $a != $c1 and $a != $c2;

BEGIN_TEXT
Suppose \(f\) and \(g\) are continuous functions such that \(g($a)=$c1\)
and such that \(f\) is defined at \(x=$a\).  Assume also that
\[ \lim_{x \to $a} [$c2 f(x) + f(x)g(x)] = $c3\;. \]
Find \(f($a)\).
$PAR
\(f($a)\) = \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
$BR
END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($ans));

BEGIN_SOLUTION
$SOL
The function \($c2 f(x) + f(x)g(x)\) is continuous at \(x=$a\),
so the equation simplifies to
\[ $c2 f($a) + f($a)g($a) = $c3\;. \]
One can then solve for \(f($a)\) using the known value for \(g($a)\).
END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
